From a7765aa398595e56f6192e24320eeef98e79bc05 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Harish Rachakonda <rachakon@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Fri, 1 Aug 2025 09:55:27 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] QSDK:CP:hostapd: ATF: add peer specific commands and show
 commands

This patch introduces new CLI commands to manage airtime fairness at
both station and group levels.
The following commands are added:

addsta - Add a new station with airtime configuration.
delsta - Delete an existing station's airtime configuration.
showairtime - Display all configured station mac aaddress
	      and airtime configured.
showatftable - Show all configured groups and their associated
	       peers with airtime info.
flushatftable - Flush all configured airtime entries
		     (stations and groups)
cli commands:
MLO:
hostapd_cli  -i <ifname> [-l <link_id>] atf_offload  addsta <stamacaddr>
<airtime %> <Group_name/SSID>
hostapd_cli  -i <ifname> [-l <link_id>] atf_offload delsta  <stamacaddr>
hostapd_cli  -i <ifname> [-l <link_id>] atf_offload showatftable
hostapd_cli  -i <ifname> [-l <link_id>] atf_offload  showairtime
hostapd_cli  -i <ifname> [-l <link_id>] atf_offload  flushatftable
Legacy:
hostapd_cli  -i <ifname> atf_offload  addsta <stamacaddr> <airtime %>
<Group_name/SSID>
hostapd_cli  -i <ifname> atf_offload delsta  <stamacaddr>
hostapd_cli  -i <ifname> atf_offload showatftable
hostapd_cli  -i <ifname> atf_offload  showairtime
hostapd_cli  -i <ifname> atf_offload  flushatftable

Signed-off-by: Harish Rachakonda <rachakon@qti.qualcomm.com>
